OK, keep moving. Now things will begin to get interesting. These latter two classes are harder conceptually, but once you have a solution method for them, they're not all that hard. This one is the problem I described at the beginning. We've got this hockey puck like thing. And the string wrapped around it pulling on it with a known force. In this problem, they call it 150 newtons.

