What's that? Well, this looks like a definition of angular momentum. This is the angular momentum of every little mass particle with respect to G added up. This is H with respect to G, which is what we set out to prove. So the H with respect to A is H with respect to G plus RGA cross the linear momentum of the body. Yeah.

